inlineContent.text: Not all property values exist for all file system URLs. For example, if a file is located on a volume that doesn’t support creation dates, you can request the creation date property, but the request returns
Only the fields requested by the keys you pass into the
function to receive this value will be populated. The other fields return
regardless of the underlying property on the file system.
As a convenience, you can request volume resource values from any file system URL. The value returned reflects the property value for the volume that the resource is located on.
